Actor, Ibrahim Suleiman has opened up on one of the ‘wrong things’ he’s glad to have done with his wife before marriage. The movie act, who is married to his colleague, Ihuoma Linda Ejiofor, revealed this while reacting to a lady’s post on Twitter who reminded Christians that it is wrong cohabiting with a partner before marriage. “A subtle reminder that as a Christian, cohabiting with your partner before marriage is wrong,” she tweeted. Responding to the tweet, Suleiman affirmed it to be true. However, he also admitted to be ‘guilty’ of the above stated but noted it was one wrong decision he’s entirely glad to have made.   Funke Akindele’s ‘Omo Ghetto The Saga’ becomes most watched…     Yul Edochie begs FG to release Nnamdi Kanu     My best moment don’t make it to social media – Nengi   - Advertisement - The father-of-one went further to state reasons why he cohabited with his wife, before marriage. “This is true. But it is one of the wrong things I’m glad I did even if it was just for a few weeks. It just felt like the natural/wise thing to do. Get to spend time in each other’s faces, day in, day out”, he tweeted. “We are both ambiverts who value alone time so it was important to learn each other’s cues. Now I can tell when she needs a couple of hours to herself and vice versa. “Look, I’ve never been one to give a false impression of piety. But once in a while…own your transgressions with your chest.” SPONSORED